  urldate = {2026-04-23},
  abstract = {As a result of the enormous advances in molecular biology, recombinant technology, and genomics over the past few decades, target-based drug discovery has become the dominant technique employed by numerous pharmaceutical businesses. However, despite increasing investment from pharmaceutical companies, the target-based drug discovery technique has not led to a concurrent increase in the number of unique molecular components or the identification of specific biological products despite being advantageous in terms of throughput and prices. Identification of more molecular targets has been made easier by developments in chemical and molecular biology, which has necessitated the creation of innovative screening techniques. It is due to major improvements in several phenotypic screening technologies, which this procedure of target-based screening has experienced a setback in the pharmaceutical sector. Therefore, for bridging the gap in between target-based approaches, phenotypic approaches, and other relevant drug discovery approaches, the idea of integrating the greatest qualities from different drug discovery methodologies has been a savior. This book chapter describes all these drug screening strategies in brief.},
